HEADWORD: litigatious
<hw>litigatious</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>of or pertaining
to litigation.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> litiginous.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>prone to initiate litigation.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> litiginous.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>same as <er>contentious</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> litigatious, litiginous, contentious, disputatious;
quarrelsome; argumentative.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

